[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two jailed after canister incident at Stafford McDonald's

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two men who set off a canister in a fast-food restaurant have been jailed for 10 months each.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two girls aged 17 and 18, were taken to Royal Stoke University Hospital with respiratory and abdominal issues.
Christopher Wardle, 25, formerly of Barrack Road, Newcastle-upon-Tyne, and Spencer Benham, 23, of Wilberforce Road, Leicester, pleaded guilty to possessing a prohibited weapon.
They were sentenced at Stafford Crown Court on 15 July.
